{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "615454d770a8e4290161e002", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d70f9a489afa3080ade2d"], "chapters": ["615d6ff12b295b085ab6ebfe"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "91", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "The glomerular area of the adrenal cortex is mainly responsible for", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "yApnu", "text": "maintaining glucose levels", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "pnt0e", "text": "carbohydrate metabolism", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "USb04", "text": "water and electrolyte balance", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "q8JQx", "text": "steroid and hormone secretion", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "Adrenals glands located on the kidneys produce a variety of hormones. Adrenal gland is divided into two parts - adrenal cortex and adrenal medulla (innermost layer). Cortex is further divided into zona glomerulosa, zona fasciculata and zona reticularis. <br/><br/>Zona glomerulosa is the outermost layer and responsible for production of aldosterone that is a mineralocorticoid which maintains electrolyte and water balance in the body.<br/><br/>Carbohydrate metabolism is regulated by glucocorticoids secreted by the zona fasciculata of adrenal cortex. <br/><br/>Zona reticularis is responsible for secretion steroidal hormones.", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["616057290283de43c87e3e1a", "616057b00283de43c87e3e20", "64d50cd33df7f